  "text": "In (3.1), we employ the following decomposition of the plain wave e −ikx into the dipole-approximated term e −ik0 = 1 and the error term e −ikx − 1, i.e., (3.6) e −ikx = 1 + (e −ikx − 1), because this decomposition provides very simple treatment to estimate the total number of soft bosons. Dereziński and Gérard implement this way in L 2 -theory [CITATION_1] . We also employ this way and implement it in operator theory by using (3.3).",
